 Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Weston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from any of numerous places called Weston, from Old English <i>west</i> ‘west’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’.","topographic name from Middle English <i>atte west tun(e)</i> ‘at the west farmstead, settlement’ (Old English <i>west</i> + <i>tūn</i>), or from Middle English <i>(bi) weste(n)tune</i> (Old English <i>be westan tūne</i> or <i>be west in tūne</i>), denoting someone who lived either to the west of a settlement or in the western part of a settlement. The latter was a common surname in Sussex."],"variants":[{"name":"Wesson","meanings":["English (Midlands and Kent): variant of   Weston  .","History: John Wesson came from England to Salem, MA, in 1644."]}]},{"name":"Hamon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Raimundo .   See  <b>Raymond</b>   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hamon de Weston was born in 1136, in Weston under Lizard, Staffordshire, England, his father, Robert de Weston, was 23 and his mother, Sibyl de Landa, was 21. He married Maud of Surrey in 1169, in Merton, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 16 October 1214, in Weston, Staffordshire, Engl